node.text:
Answering lots of questions I’ve been receiving about my new weekly newsletters.
Link for this set- https://bit.ly/weeklynewsletters

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on September 07, 2021.

node.text: The beginning of the year is a great time for narrative writing! These books are perfect for narratives or story writing! The rubrics make them easy to grade and help guide your students as they write. PS the rubrics are editable for you to customize. 🙌🏽 Link in profile: https://bit.ly/storywritingbooks

node.text:
These little comprehension books have come in so handy over the years! I suggest keeping multiple copies of each one on hand so you can pull them out at a moment’s notice!

This resource includes digital and Spanish copies too! My kids loved them every year! Link in profile: http://bit.ly/minicomprehensionbooks

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on September 05, 2021 tagging @learninginwonderland, @crayola, @melonheadzillustrating, @teacherspayteachers, and @the_happy_planner.

node.text: You saw the color version of these lesson plan templates other day, but how stunning do they look in black & white? 😍 Both versions are included for you to choose from. The one page layout also includes color and b&w copies! Link in bio- in profile: https://bit.ly/liwlessonplans

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on September 05, 2021.

node.text: This @cricut project is still one of my all time favorites! I used some clip art from @melonheadzillustrating and removable vinyl to put it together. The kids thought it was so fun!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on September 04, 2021.

node.text:
I released some lesson plan templates earlier this week with my kids theme. Some of my chunky chevron lovers reached out and asked if I could make some with this theme and I was happy to get those made.

If you already own the chunky chevron collection, please re-download to get this new addition. If you just want to pick up this set of templates, you can grab them with the link in profile- https://bit.ly/chunkychevlessonplans

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on September 03, 2021.

node.text: I sent this label out a few weeks ago to all Wonderland Newsletter subscribers, but you can still grab a free copy if you missed it. Link in profile- https://bit.ly/rulerfreebie

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on September 02, 2021.

node.text: I shared my two page lesson plan layout the other day, but I’m also loving these one page layouts! I made sure to include the sticky note area on top still because I find that so useful. These include editable and black and white copies too! Link in profile: https://bit.ly/liwlessonplans

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
Heads up to those of you who own my planner basics and planner essentials bundles!

Go re-download because I added a new resource to both of them yesterday! If you have been considering purchasing either bundle, make sure to use code BTSBONUS21 to grab them 25% off today!

PS I’m also getting a lot of questions about the planner I add my inserts to. I’m a huge fan of @the_happy_planner! I picked this one up at Walmart, but you can find them at any craft store too!

Link in profile for the basics bundle- http://bit.ly/plannerbasics

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on August 31, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
🥳 New and on SALE!!!!🥳 I’ve received so many requests for lesson plan templates over the years! I’m so happy to have these done and ready to go for you!

One of my favorite parts is the sticky note area up on top. I always needed this on my lesson plans so I made sure to include that. Link in profile: https://bit.ly/liwlessonplans

node.text: These comprehension mini books are some of my favorite things to use in the classroom and FYI... the Spanish versions are coming soon! 🤩 Let me know if you want to be tagged when they are ready. 😊 Link in profile- http://bit.ly/minicomprehensionbooks

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on August 28, 2021 tagging @walmart, and @crayola. May be an image of cosmetics.

node.text: These @crayola Clicks are just so beautiful!! I’m using them just about every day. I got the 20 pack from @walmart and it includes all the colors 😍 I’d say these are perfect for grading and writing notes on student papers. I wouldn’t suggest these for anchor charts because they write on the thinner side. I’d compare them to Fine Point Sharpies in terms of the tip size.
